Manage Queries for Widgets
Queries return results that are displayed in widgets. For example, a number widget displays the result of a calculation that is defined in a query.
Queries can be built on a data source or created with user-defined values.

You can create a query by clipping a lens from an exploration, using the widget wizard, or creating a query manually in dashboard designer.
Behind the scenes, CRM Analytics assigns a unique ID to each query in the dashboard.

To improve dashboard performance, minimize the number of queries in a dashboard. When possible, reuse a query for multiple widgets.
Queries and Custom Queries
Widgets that display data require queries.
Create a Query with a Lens
Manually create a query from the dashboard designer when you're concerned about the results it returns and not the widget that displays those results.
Create a Query with the Query Editor
Use the query editor to create or customize SAQL or SOQL queries.
Create a Custom Query with User-Defined Values
Use custom queries to apply user-defined values to dimensions, measures, and limits of other queries.

Find a Query
Edit a Query
When you edit a query, you can change the details, like the query label. These changes affect all widgets that use the query.
Clone a Query
Clone a query to quickly create a query based on an existing one.
Modify the Query Results Based on the Dashboard Viewer
You can modify a query based on the user viewing the dashboard.

Optimize a Query
Queries can slow down your dashboard. Run a performance check on the queries to ensure that they’re running optimally.
Considerations for Queries with Multiple Datasets
When a query has multiple datasets, the query results are formatted using the XMD of the first loaded dataset.
Troubleshoot Unexpected Query Results
If you have questions about a query’s results, review the query details to learn how CRM Analytics determines the results.

Query Properties for Analytics Dashboard
Query properties define the query that returns results to display in the widget. These properties also specify how the widget behaves and interacts with other widgets in the CRM Analytics dashboard.
